    "department": "Design",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nAs a Staff Design Systems Designer, you will define the foundations that make Harvey’s product coherent, scalable, and trustworthy as it grows in complexity. The design system is not just a library of components—it is the shared language between design, engineering, and AI that ensures consistency, quality, and confidence across every interaction.\n\nIn this role, you will operate as both a systems thinker and hands-on builder. Working in close partnership with frontend and platform engineering, you will design, ship, and evolve the components, patterns, and tokens that power the product. Your work will directly shape how quickly teams can build, how reliably the product behaves, and how confidently users interact with AI-driven workflows.\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Define and evolve the core design system foundations, including components, patterns, and tokens that scale across complex, AI-powered experiences\n\n - Design, prototype, and ship production-ready system components in tight collaboration with frontend engineering\n\n - Partner directly with frontend and platform engineers to ensure system decisions translate cleanly into code, with shared ownership of quality, performance, and maintainability\n\n - Establish clear contribution, governance, and deprecation models that balance velocity with system integrity\n\n - Embed accessibility, responsiveness, and performance into the system by default\n\n - Document system usage and best practices in a way that is clear, practical, and trusted by product teams\n\n - Advocate for system adoption and consistency in product planning, design reviews, and execution\n\n - Anticipate future product and platform needs, evolving the system proactively as Harvey scales\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - 8+ years of experience in product design, with significant ownership of design systems in complex product environments\n\n - An excelelnt portfolio demonstrating system-level thinking, component design, and real product impact\n\n - Deep understanding of component architecture, design tokens, and how design systems scale across teams\n\n - Proven experience partnering closely with frontend engineers to ship high-quality, production systems\n\n - Strong working knowledge of accessibility standards and inclusive design practices\n\n - Ability to clearly articulate system decisions and tradeoffs to designers, engineers, and cross-functional partners\n\n - Comfort operating in ambiguous problem spaces and bringing structure where it doesn’t yet exist\n\n\nWHY DESIGN SYSTEMS MATTER AT HARVEY\n\nHarvey is an AI-native product. As the system reasons, responds, and adapts in real time, the interface must remain consistent and legible. A strong design system ensures that complexity does not leak into the experience. It enables teams to move faster, reduces cognitive load for users, and builds trust in moments where clarity matters most.\n\n\nCOMPENSATION\n\n$200,000 - $260,000 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-JC1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
